title: Inovation foundation Techathon 2.0
description: I had the incredible opportunity to participate in InnovateYou Techathon 2.0, a 24-hour national-level hackathon at AISSMS IOIT Pune, organized by the Innovation Foundation, Pune. Our challenge was to develop an AI-driven solution for quick and accurate patient record analysis, pushing us to innovate under pressure. It was an intense yet rewarding experience, filled with brainstorming, coding, and last-minute debugging. Being part of such a competitive and insightful event, judged by industry experts, was truly inspiring. Looking forward to more such challenges!

title: Nirman X ODOO Hackathon
description: From a fun, no-expectations start to securing a Top 7 spot, our hackathon journey at Amity University Mumbai was pure chaos and innovation! With top-notch management, great vibes, and intense problem statements from Odoo, we tackled merge conflicts, database nightmares, and UI disasters—all while running on caffeine and last-minute panic. Somehow, we made it through! Shoutout to my incredible team, Rudra, Atharva, and Adnan, for making the impossible happen. Here’s to more hackathons, more challenges, and, let’s be real, more last-minute submissions!

title: Smart Cities Urban Planning & Management

I’m thrilled to share that I’ve just completed a course on Smart Cities! This journey has enriched my understanding of urban infrastructure and the principles of urban management.
I delved into the key components that create a smart urban infrastructure system, focusing on smart transport and energy solutions. The case studies from around the globe provided valuable insights into innovative urban planning practices.
I can’t wait to apply this knowledge and contribute to building smarter, more sustainable cities. Stay tuned for more insights on this fascinating topic!

title: Angular
description: Angular is the most powerful UI framework which can be used to develop complex, customizable, modern, responsive, and user-friendly web applications. The angular framework follows a component-oriented application design pattern to develop completely reusable and modularized web applications. This course introduces learners to various concepts like creating components, enhancing the functionality of components, sharing data between the components, validating forms, communicating with backend code, and building a single-page application using synchronous or asynchronous routing
